ce:section.ce:para:
Raman spectrum was applied to characterize the microstructure of N-CDs. Two typical peaks are shown in Fig. 3
                        a, corresponding to a disordered D band at 1368cm−1 and a crystalline G band at 1575cm−1, respectively. The D band is related to the presence of sp3 defects, while the G band is associated with in-plane vibration of sp2 carbon [25]. The intensity ratio of the D band and G band (ID/IG
                        ) of N-CDs160-1, N-CDs200-1 and N-CDs200-2 are 0.82, 0.87 and 0.84, respectively. N-CDs200-1 show a relatively high disorder since they are middle products of the transition from polymer state to carbon nuclear state.
